    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">	I put a larger version of this deck on earlier but I have taken your advice and shrank it from 86 to 72.  So please tell me what you think.<br />
    Thanks.<br />
<br />
Free Peoples Strategy<br />
	If you go first, play Preparations with your site.  You can put Honed on Preparations so you can play it with Sindri’s text.  Also, use Slaked Thirsts to draw a card; then, in the regroup, exert a dwarf to put it on Preparations for anti grima.  Put possessions/artifacts on Durin III  to boost him up.  Get Aggression down to draw cards   Use Nobody Tosses a Dwarf to discard the shadow player’s cards off of his/her draw deck then your next turn use Ring of Guile to get Nobody Tosses a Dwarf back.  Increase damage with Lord of Moria, Aggression, and Ring of Fury for Blood Runs Chill, Gimli’s resistance, and Honed.  Blood Runs Chill gets rid of shadow conditions, possessions, minions, and artifacts.<br />
<br />
Shadow Strategy<br />
Morgul Hunter is for vitality, so you can play your Tower of Barad-Dur, Ithil Stone, the irresistible shadow, desperate defense of the ring, Thin and stretched, and his cruelty and malice.  Use Grishnakh for drawing cards or adding burdens, as well as to make the site number of the orcs mines three.  Thin and stretched is to get burden for the Irresistible Shadow and Desperate Measures.  Desperate Defense of the Ring is to discard cards or add burdens.  Tower of Barad-Dur is to discard cards from the free people’s hand every time they move.  Ithil Stone is to draw a card every shadow phase and play one minion for mines three.  Orc warrior is for uses at later sites to finish off the free people’s draw deck for Irresistible Shadow or moving your fellowship to site nine with no minions to stop you.  <br />
<br />
